cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper combines text and image-based representations to produce sparse, interpretable vectors for modeling human conceptual knowledge. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including natural language processing (cs.CL), computer vision (cs.CV), machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). However, given the focus on distributional models and semantic embeddings, as well as the use of text data, cs.CL is the most likely category.
